commitResults.messageTitle: UI: Render person tags as dark blue bubbles
commitResults.messageBody:
Person tags currently share delivery tag styling, which makes it hard to
distinguish at a glance who the tags belong to in the UI.

Make person (client) tags display as separate dark-blue bubbles so they
are visually distinct from delivery tags and easier to scan in lists.
This keeps delivery pills unchanged.

commitResults.messageTitle: Docs: align UserGuide with v0.3 command set
commitResults.messageBody:
Synchronize command names, formats, and wording with v0.3 release
notes so the guide matches current behavior. Update examples,
command summaries, and tips; clarify case-sensitive prefixes and
date/time formats; note tag colour behavior (Personal/Corporate).
Also tighten Quick Start and Troubleshooting for first-time users.

This improves accuracy and reduces confusion between docs and the
app UI/CLI.

commitResults.messageTitle: Docs: update Storage UML to include DeliveryBook
commitResults.messageBody:
Add DeliveryBook storage to the Storage UML:
- New interface: DeliveryBookStorage
- Implementations: JsonDeliveryBookStorage, JsonSerializableDeliveryBook
- Adapter: JsonAdaptedDelivery
- Wire StorageManager to DeliveryBookStorage
- Show JsonAdaptedDelivery referencing JsonAdaptedPerson

This keeps the diagram in sync with the current codebase, improves
accuracy for readers, and reduces onboarding confusion.

No production code changes.

commitResults.messageTitle: Docs: update Storage UML to reflect FoodBook architecture
commitResults.messageBody:
Update the Storage UML diagram to match the current implementation:
- Replace AddressBook storage with FoodBook storage
- Add FoodBookStorage, JsonFoodBookStorage, JsonSerializableFoodBook
- Include JsonAdaptedPerson, JsonAdaptedDelivery, and JsonAdaptedTag
- Retain UserPrefsStorage and JsonUserPrefsStorage
- Show StorageManager managing both FoodBook and UserPrefs storages

This improves documentation accuracy and helps new contributors
understand the updated storage layer structure.
